      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/58956e/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2023-07-31T21:12:09.434Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi there,</p>\n<p>I\u2019m new to cycling and new to trainer day. I\u2019m using the Tacx Flux S and just tried to the FTP ramp test and noticed that the wattage seemed really inconsistent on ERG mode. For example when the target wattage was 300+ sometimes my actual wattage would drop to as low as 95 and then jump back up to a wattage higher than the target wattage. Sometimes at times I would feel as though it was easy and then in the same interval it suddenly feels harder. Whilst the wattage did drop low my heart rate did continue to climb up to 183 at which point I stopped and got an FTP of 214. Unsure whether this FTP is accurate given the issues noted above.</p>\n<p>Apologies if this is something really obvious, but being new to cycling I\u2019m unsure whether this is normal or not.</p>\n<p>Thanks,<br>\nTom</p>",
